<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 3:48PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
west central Pulaski, east central Smyth, Bland, Wythe and north
central Grayson Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 348 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rural Retreat, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Bland...
Rural Retreat...
Max Meadows...
Rocky Gap...
Speedwell...
and Bastian.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
